<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Around line 290 in Zend/XmlRpc/Fault.php:</p>

<pre><code>    // Build response XML
    $dom  = new DOMDocument('1.0', 'ISO-8859-1');
</code></pre>

<p>Should read:</p>

<pre><code>    // Build response XML
    $dom  = new DOMDocument('1.0', $this-&gt;getEncoding());
</code></pre>

<p>Otherwise encoding of fault XML is always ISO-8859-1, overwriting default charset of UTF-8 and making calls to setEncoding() useless.</p>

